value.value: The cell cycle process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome are joined along the length of the chromosome arms during mitosis.
The cell cycle process in which centromeres of sister chromatids are joined during mitosis.

A vesicle-mediated transport process in which transmembrane proteins are ubiquitylated to facilitate their entry into luminal vesicles of multivesicular bodies (MVBs); upon subsequent fusion of MVBs with lysosomes or vacuoles, the cargo proteins are degraded.

label.value: protein localization to spindle pole body

value.value: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, the spindle pole body.

label.value: maintenance of protein location to spindle pole body

value.value: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location at the spindle pole body, and is prevented from moving elsewhere.
The directed movement of glutathione into the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
A developmental process that results in the discharge of ascospores from the ascus. Ascospore release may be active or passive.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of polysaccharides used in extracellular structures.

label.value: extracellular polysaccharide catabolic process involved in ascospore release from ascus

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of polysaccharides in the ascus wall that contributes to the release of ascospores from the ascus.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (-COOH) group.
The process in which UDP-galactose is transported across a membrane.

definition.value: Note that this term is not intended for use in annotating lateral movement within membranes.

value.value: The directed movement of modified amino acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.
The directed movement of compounds that contain sulfur, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

The directed movement of an organelle along a microtubule, mediated by motor proteins. This process begins with the attachment of an organelle to a microtubule, and ends when the organelle reaches its final destination.

label.value: microtubule anchoring at microtubule organizing center

value.value: Any process in which a microtubule is maintained in a specific location in a cell by attachment to a microtubule organizing center.

label.value: response to cell cycle checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of cell cycle checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to DNA integrity checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of DNA integrity checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to mitotic cell cycle checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of mitotic cell cycle checkpoint signaling.
A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of spindle checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to DNA damage checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of DNA damage checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to G2 DNA damage checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of G2/M transition DNA damage checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to intra-S DNA damage checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of intra-S DNA damage checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of mitotic G2/M transition DNA damage checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to mitotic spindle checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of mitotic cell cycle spindle checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint signaling.

label.value: response to spindle assembly checkpoint signaling

value.value: A process that occurs in response to signals generated as a result of spindle assembly checkpoint signaling.
The chemical reactions and pathways involving a purine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains purine or a formal derivative thereof.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a purine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains purine or a formal derivative thereof.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a purine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains purine or a formal derivative thereof.
The chemical reactions and pathways involving a pyridine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains pyridine or a formal derivative thereof.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a pyridine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains pyridine or a formal derivative thereof.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a pyridine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains pyridine or a formal derivative thereof.
The chemical reactions and pathways involving a pyrimidine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains pyrimidine or a formal derivative thereof.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a pyrimidine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains pyrimidine or a formal derivative thereof.
The process in which a purine-containing compound is transported across a membrane. A purine-containing compound is any compound that contains purine or a formal derivative thereof.

definition.value: Note that this term is not intended for use in annotating lateral movement within membranes.

value.value: The process in which a pyrimidine-containing compound is transported across a membrane. A pyrimidine-containing compound is any compound that contains pyrimidine or a formal derivative thereof.

definition.value: Note that this term is not intended for use in annotating lateral movement within membranes.

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a reactive oxygen species, any molecules or ions formed by the incomplete one-electron reduction of oxygen. They contribute to the microbicidal activity of phagocytes, regulation of signal transduction and gene expression, and the oxidative damage to biopolymers.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to organelle

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location on or in an organelle. Encompasses establishment of localization in the membrane or lumen of a membrane-bounded organelle.

label.value: maintenance of protein localization in organelle

value.value: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location a specific location on or in an organelle, and is prevented from moving elsewhere. Encompasses establishment of localization in the membrane or lumen of a membrane-bounded organelle.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in the endoplasmic reticulum.

label.value: maintenance of protein location in mitochondrion

value.value: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location in a mitochondrion, and is prevented from moving elsewhere.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location in a membrane.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location in the plasma membrane.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location in a peroxisome.

label.value: maintenance of protein location in peroxisome

value.value: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location in a peroxisome, and is prevented from moving elsewhere.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location in a vacuole.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to vacuole

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a vacuole.

label.value: maintenance of protein location in vacuole

value.value: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location in a vacuole, and is prevented from moving elsewhere.

The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an Mre11 complex, a trimeric protein complex that possesses endonuclease activity and is involved in meiotic recombination, DNA repair and checkpoint signaling.
A spindle that forms as part of mitosis. Mitotic and meiotic spindles contain distinctive complements of proteins associated with microtubules.
